ADDITION RULE :

1 ) - MUTUALLY EXCLUSIVE EVENT :

Two events are mutually  exclusive if they cannot occur at the same time . EX : Tossing a coin

P ( H or T ) = P ( H ) + P ( T )  { Additive rule for mutually exclusive events }

2 ) - NON MUTUALLY EXCLUSIVE EVENT :

EX : Taking a card from the deck

P ( K or HEART ) = P ( K ) + P ( HEART ) - P ( K and HEART )


MULTIPLICATION RULE :

1 ) - INDEPENDENT :

2 events are independent if they do not affect one another . EX : tossing a coin { first getting H and then T }

P ( H AND T ) = P ( H ) * P ( T ) = 1/2 * 1/2 = 1/4

2 ) - DEPENDENT :

2 events are dependent iff they affect each other . EX : Taking a kind out from a deck and then the queen from the deck .
P ( K ) = 4/52 , P ( Q ) = 4/51

{ Bayes Theorem / Conditional Probability } P ( K AND Q ) = P ( K ) * P ( Q / K ) = 4/52 * 4/51



