P - VALUE :

It describes how likely you are to have found a particular set of observations if the null hypothesis were true . It is used to determine
whether to reject the null hypothesis or not .

EX : tossing a coin 100 times . Ho - the coin is fair , H1 - the coin is not fair . We will get a bell curve where mean is 50 and SD = 10 .
We will set a confidence interval lets say  between 30 and 70 . So that means if we get values between 30 and 70 we can say that the coin
is fair . Outside this interval the coin is not fair .

Significance Value ( alpha ) - 0.05 . Confidence interval ( CI ) = 1-0.05 = 0.95 . So in the curve where we set the interval the area would
be 95 % CI and the rest 5 % will be divided into 2 parts left and right into 2.5 % . Lets say the p value comes in the region that belongs to
the 5 % i.e. p > Significance value ( SV ) or p < SV , then we can reject the null hypothesis . if it is present in the SV region we fail to
reject the null hypothesis .


                                Z - TEST

Z test and t test are for average values whereas Chi square is for categorical data and ANNOVA is for variance

Conditions for using Z test:

1 ) - need to know population SD    2 ) - The sample size should be greater than 30

Q - The avg height in a city is 168 cm . The SD is 3.9 cm . A doctor wants to find out if the mean is different . Measured height of 36 individuals
and found the mean to be 169.5 . what is the null and the alternate hypothesis . if the CI is 95% is there enough evidence to reject the null
hypothesis .

A - population mean ( mue ) = 168cm , sigma = 3.9 , n = 36 , xbar = 169.5 cm , CI = 0.95 , alpha = 1-0.95 = 0.05 . SV = 0.05

Ho - the avg height is 168 cm , Ha - the avg height is not 168 cm . Now based on the CI we will draw a decision boundary . This is known as
2 Tail test . To find out where we need to place this decision boundary we will find the Z score . As the distribution is symmetric if we find
z score for one end the -ve of that value will become the z score for the other end .

1 - 0.025 = 0.975 ==> Z - score . Now we need to check thi value i.e. 0.975 in the Z table and find the Z score corresponding to that . From the
table we are getting the value 1.96 Z - score . In the opposite end we get -1.96 . So if we find a statistical analysis and we get the value
between this range of Z - score then the null hypothesis is true meaning that we failed to reject the null hypothesis .

Z TEST ( Zd ) = xbar - mue / sigma/root(n) = 169.5 - 168 / 3.9 / root ( 36 ) = 2.31

Zd = 2.31 . As 2.31 > 1.96 , so we reject the null hypothesis . Now we will use this new Z score and graph another graph where we will get
the side value as 0.01044 i.e 1 - 0.98956 , this 0.9 value we got from reversing the Z score using the Z table . So the leftover area is
1 - 2 * 0.01044 = 0.97912 .

P VALUE = 0.01044 + 0.01044 = 0.02
p<0.05 ==> 0.02 < 0.05 . We need to reject the null hypothesis .

The final conclusion is that the avg height is not 168 cm . So the avg height seems to be increasing based on the sample data .

