                                            BAYES THEOREM

This is used for dependent events where conditional probability is used . Ex : Picking a K and a Q from a deck of cards

P ( K and Q ) = P ( K ) * ( P ( Q / K ) --> Probability of getting queen given King was selected )
              = 4/52 * 4/51

P ( K AND Q ) = P ( Q AND K )
P ( K ) * P ( Q/K ) = P ( Q ) * P ( K/Q )
P ( Q/K ) = P ( Q ) * P ( K/Q ) / P ( K ) ==> This equation is called bayes theorem .

Now in ML , in the Naive Bayes algorithm , lets say we have 3 independent features and the label y is dependent on them , so we implement it
using the following formula

P ( y/x1 x2 x3 ) = P ( y ) * P ( x1 x2 x3 / y ) / P ( x1 x2 x3 ) --> This is the equation for naive bayes theorem .


