                                            CONFIDENCE INTERVAL AND MARGIN OF ERROR

lets say we have a CI of 95 % . Now if the z test value lies in this CI interval we are going to accept the null hypothesis . So to find the
value of the confidence interval we will use point estimate

So lets say xbar is the point estimate to find mue . So if my xbar is 2.5 and mue is 3 . the xbar could also be greater than mue . Now this gap
between the xbar and mue is the drawback of point estimate . so to counter that we use a range or interval , in this example we set it
to 2 to 4 . meaning if the mue comes between 2 to 4 we will accept it .

Now to find this values i.e. 2 and 4 . we will use the following formula

        point estimate +- margin of error

        xbar +- Z alpha/2 * sigma / root(n) ( This is for Z test , if we are using Z test , if we are using T test we will use T alpha/2 )

EX : In the verbal section of CAT the SD =  100 . a sample of 30 tests were taken and had a mean of 520 . Construct 95% CI abput the mean

