                                            CHI SQUARE TEST

The chi square test for Goodness of fit . This test claims about population proportions . It is a non parametric test that is performed on
the categorical data .

There is a population of male that likes different colors of a bike . So the theory is 1/4 likes likes black , 1/4 likes blue
and 1/2 likes white . They collected a sample and found out 22 , 17 and 59 liked the colors respectively . So using the chi squared test we
will see if the sample data is a goodness of fit test for the theory .

Ho - The data meets the expectation . Ha - the data doesnt meet the expectation . alpha = 0.05 , CI = 95% dof = 3 -1 = 2 ( categorical )
Using the chi square table we find that the critical value is around 5.991 . If chi^2 is greater 5.991 we will reject Ho else fail to
reject Ho

Chi square ( chi^2 ) = sigma ( observed -  expected ) ^ 2 / expected
                     = ( 22-25 )^2 / 25 + ( 17-25 )^2 / 25 + ( 59-50 )^2/50
                     = 9/25 + 64/25 + 81/50
                     = 73/25 + 81/50
                     = 146+81/50
                     = 227/50
                     = 45.4

As we can se the value of chi square is gretaer than 5.991 we will reject the null hypothesis .


